</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1206,1534]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
Trees and shrubs 
<quantity box="[405,480,1321,1347]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" unit="m" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7 m</quantity>
tall. Morphologicaly similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sobral" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="DC." box="[857,1017,1321,1346]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="densa">
<emphasis box="[857,1017,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Myrcia densa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by having larger leaves (
<quantity box="[159,264,1358,1384]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" unit="cm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 cm</quantity>
long), acute calyx lobes and a pilose hypanthium; it differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1289,1358,1384]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1112,1196,1358,1383]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Myrcia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by having a non-sulcate midvein on the adaxial lamina surface, ferruginous trichomes and globose fruits.
</paragraph>
